external_knowledge:
Vast fields: fields with an area greater than 100 hectares;
Expansive farms: farms with a total area greater than 1000 hectares;
Slow-growing crops: those with a growth period longer than 120 days;
Most productive: ordered by yield measurement in descending order.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(farm_id) 
FROM farms 
WHERE establishment_date > '2000-01-01';

SELECT farm_name
FROM farms
WHERE farm_id = 1;

SELECT DISTINCT crop_name, growth_period
FROM crops
WHERE optimal_soil_type = 'Clay' AND common_pests = 'None';

external_knowledge:
'Growing phase' refers to the 'Vegetative' stage in crop development;
'Viewed' means the access type is 'view' in the database;
'Farms located in the USA' refers to farms with the location 'USA';
'Farmer' is one of the roles a user can have, and it must be checked in a case-insensitive manner.
